name: USACO Silver Contest
description: Scored 800/1000 and promoted to Gold
detailedDescription:
Scored 800/1000 and ranked 574/3410 of precollege students. Achieved promotion to the Gold Division in the USA Computing Olympiad (USACO), a prestigious competitive programming contest for high school students.

The Gold Division involves advanced algorithms and data structures including segment trees, network flow, and dynamic programming techniques. You can find my solutions on my github at riddhimanrana/usaco-solutions

name: 3M Young Scientist Challenge
description: Participated in the 3M Young Scientist Challenge with a project on energy efficiency
detailedDescription:
Participated in the 3M Young Scientist Challenge, a prestigious national competition that encourages elementary and middle school students to showcase their scientific research and innovation.

My project was basically about how we can take the heat that our laptops and computers produce and use a small TEG(Thermo Electric Generator) to use that to give back power to our laptops, similar to how regenerative braking works on electric vehicles. This could potentially reduce our energy impact and carbon emissions for many everyday items if it can be produced and implemented into real world items in an efficient and production ready design.

Although I didn’t win anything in this contest, it was an incredible experience that taught me a lot and introduced me to the world of science and research.
